<dl id="n03160u"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03160u">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03160u"> 160(u)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Athlete flogged</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It is a changed world into which the literature of medieval Ireland ushers us. The old magnificence is there, but it is a secondary theme. The great military encampments have been eclipsed by the sudden mustering of new legionaries&mdash;champions of wisdom, milites Christi, <mark>athletes of asceticism</mark>, sages, prophets and saints. <small> Benedict Fitzpatrick, <a name="BFIM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BFIM"><cite title="source">Ireland and the Making of Britain</cite></a> (1922) 112</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
